observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the Municipal Accountant, the Municipal Health Office, and other concerned offices to submit the following documents:
The list of public health workers, including Barangay Health Workers, determined and approved by the Local Health Board;
Specific authority from the head of the agency to the claimants to physically report and respond to the public health emergency during the state of national emergency indicating therein the assigned work stations/health facilities for COVID-19, the prescribed official working hours, and their duties and responsibilities;
Daily Time Records showing the actual date and time of the services rendered by the claimants as certified by the head of hospital, laboratory, or medical and quarantine facility, or his/her authorized representative;
Certification attesting to the truthfulness of the contents of the report and adequate consent for sharing of data obtained from the personnel involved. The certification must be signed by the head of human resource or personnel division and the head of the health facility, clearly indicating his/her designation or position; and,
Accomplishment Reports showing that the claimants have provided direct treatment and support care to COVID-19 patients.

We recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following course of actions:

Require the Municipal Health Office to furnish the Municipal Accounting Office certified copies of the Property Transfer Reports of all vaccines, drugs and medicines, medical and other supplies, and medical equipment received from the DOH-DCHD;

Require also the Rural Health Unit (RHU) to submit a Summary Report of the Issuance/Distribution of vaccines, drugs and medicines, medical and other supplies in CY2020 and showing the inventories at hand as of December 31, 2020;

Require the General Services Office to issue of Acknowledgement Receipt of Equipment and record the equipment received by the RHU;

Require the Municipal Accounting Office to record in the specific Inventories accounts the cost of inventories at hand as of December 31, 2020, if any, and record in the specific Property, plant and equipment accounts the cost and the depreciation of the equipment; and,

Establish specific policy guidelines for the receipt of properties through donations or any kind of transfer without cost to ensure proper reporting, accounting and monitoring thereof.

